overnance and to what extent it correlates with socioeconomic variables.This comprehensive study is based on interviews in Argentina, Bulgaria, Chile, China, India, Indonesia, Jordan, Kyrgyzstan, Mongolia, Pakistan, Peru, Philippines, Russia, Tanzania, Thailand, and Togo.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aComparative governmentxResearch. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / African.2bisacsh1 aCourt, Julius, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMease, Kenneth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637383940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626373839423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626373839/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK